                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38p5vw5p/manifest/annotation/p1",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>Phil.</placeName>\n                <date>July 28/56</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Revd Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Enclosed please find<lb/> my check for $25. Endeavour to secure<lb/>\n                the Book <persName>Mrs Arnold</persName> spoke of<lb/> the name of which I have\n                forgotten</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Mayer Arnold</persName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">pr Sna<add>?</add></p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p>Find also $25 from me the object for<lb/> which it is, is expressed in the list\n                whereon<lb/> my name is signed, namely, to distribute the<lb/> amt in cheap bibles\n                as you may deem proper<lb/> and I wish it to be considered an unusual<lb/>\n                subscription subject to such increase as<lb/> I may feel able to afford. Let me know\n                the<lb/> amt of <persName>Moses Gimbel's</persName> (of\n                    <placeName>Vincennes</placeName>) debt<lb/> he is here for a few days &amp;\n                wishes to pay &amp; if<lb/> you will leave a list of such of our custom</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p38p5vw5p/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
